claim.claim-text:
A method to produce recombinant MV particles for the preparation of an anti-dengue virus vaccine, comprising or consisting of:
a) transfecting a recombinant MV genome vector according to any one of claims 7 to 9, in a helper cell line which expresses the T7 RNA polymerase and the N, P and L proteins of MV;
b) transferring said helper cell line onto cells competent to sustain the replication and production of recombinant MV particles expressing a chimeric polyepitope according to any one of claims 1 to 3 and optionally a polypeptide comprising a tetravalent DENV antigen composed of the fusion of the EDI polypeptides of the four serotypes, fused to ectoM of DENV1, in particular DENV antigens having the sequence of SEQ ID NO: 145 and;
c) recovering the recombinant MV particles produced in step b).
